e tax all play a large role in the balance of wealth. Dead Hands uncovers the tremendous social and legal importance of this rite of passage, and how it reflects changing values and priorities in American families and society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aInheritance and successionxHistoryxUnited States. 0aInheritance and successionxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aInheritance and successionxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aInheritance and successionzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSuccessions et héritagesxAspect socialxÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 0aSuccessions et héritagesxHistoirexÉtats-Unis. 7aLAW / Legal History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477108540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804771085423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804771085/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles